data.text:
2015-16 (Junior)

Finished T-29th at the Primland Collegiate Invitational in September, his only event of the season before suffering a season-ending injury.

2014-15 (Sophomore)

Earned a 19th-place finish and tied teammate Andrew Winters and the Marshall Invitational, shooting a 2-over 215 for the tournament...Finished in a tie for 42nd at 7-over par at the Primland Collegiate Invitational playing as an individual...Came in 76th at the Bank of Tennessee Intercollegiate as an individual, shooting an 11-over 155 in two rounds of play...Shot a 226 in the Querencia Cabo Invitational, part of a Wake Forest 11th place finish in the tournament...Finished in the top 15 with a 7-under 209 at the Schenkel Invitational, helping Wake forest finish fifth overall...Also finished in the top 15 at The Hootie at Bulls Bay with a 4-under 212...Tied for 50th at the Yale Spring Invitational, a tournament which the Deacons won by 28 strokes.

2013-14 (Freshman)

Played in six events in his first season and notched a scoring average of 75.76 ... Four of the six rounds he played for the team counted towards the team score ... Started his career with rounds of 75-80-74 at the Carpet Capital Collegiate Classic and finished 61st at 13-over par ... Played for the team at the Collegiate Challenge Cup and finished 39th after rounds of 76-73-79 ... Returned scores of 80-73 (+13) at the O'Briant-Jensen and finished tied for 22nd ... Had a solid showing at the first event of the spring, the USA Individual Tournament, finishing tied for fourth after posting scores of 77-73-72 (+9) ... Played as an individual at the San Diego Classic and was tied for 63rd at 18-over par ... Had another good finish playing as an individual at the Irish Creek Collegiate, carding rounds of 77-72-73 (+9) and finishing tied for 30th.
